Actress, Omalicha Elom is not pleased with reports that female celebrities, especially actresses and sleeping with married men to fund their luxurious lifestyles. In a chat with Inside Nollywood, Ms. Elom warned those who are guilty to desist from the act or face the consequences. “Whatsoever a man soweth so shall he reap and whatever goes around comes around! That is the law of karma. These actresses should continue sleeping with married men and ruining marriages. When it happens to them, they shouldn’t complain,” she warned. Meanwhile, on Monday, December 16, the fast-rising movie starlet clocked 24. Expressing how she feels adding a new year, she says she is excited to have found love in 2019. “I feel like I am getting old. It is good to add another chapter in your life but I just wish time could slow down because there are so many things I would like to achieve before I turn 30. I am also very thankful for what I have achieved and accomplished at this age. I have learnt a lot too; to be more patient, tolerable and not give a reaction to every situation. In 2019, I found love. I learned to invest more and live unapologetically. I have also found happiness and peace of mind.”